---

## üßÆ Core Algorithms

### Algorithm 1: Graph Surgery (XOR-based)

For each lost photon, performs **Local Complementation (œÑ_a)** to repair the graph state:

```python
# Invert edges between neighbors of lost node a
adj_matrix[neighbors(a), neighbors(a)] ^= 1
```

### Algorithm 2: Recursive Tensor Slicing

Automatic memory management:

```
Intermediate tensor > Available RAM?
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ YES ‚Üí Cut highest-centrality bond
‚îÇ         ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Branch 0: index=0
‚îÇ         ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Branch 1: index=1
‚îÇ         ‚Üí Parallel execution via ProcessPoolExecutor
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ NO  ‚Üí Direct contraction
```

### Algorithm 3: Fidelity Estimation

$$F_{final} = \prod (1 - p_{gate})^{n_{gates}} \times \exp\left(-\sum \text{loss\_paths}\right)$$

---

## ‚ö° Performance

| Lattice | Qubits | Time (8-core) | Memory |
|---------|--------|---------------|--------|
| 4√ó4 Cluster | 16 | 0.07s | < 1 GB |
| 5√ó5 Cluster | 25 | ~62s | ~2 GB |
| 3D RHG 2√ó2√ó2 | 18 | 0.21s | < 1 GB |

*Benchmarked on Intel Core i7*

